name: ZWE
description: Small, cozy jazz club with living room atmosphere in Leopoldstadt district. Features LIVE Jazz every night with concerts and jam sessions from local and international acts. Highly rated venue for jazz enthusiasts.

name: Zoku
description: Rooftop bar and restaurant on 7th floor offering 360-degree views over Vienna. Features Living Kitchen restaurant and Kindred Spirits bar. Serves breakfast, brunch, lunch and dinner with rooftop social spaces. Located next to Prater.
opening_hours: Breakfast: Daily 07:00-10:00, Brunch: Sat-Sun 11:00-14:00, Bar: dusk till dawn

name: City Bar
description: Stylish and modern gay bar located across from legendary Why Not discotheque. Exudes fun, friendly vibe serving tasty cocktails, great music, and regular drink specials. Features daily happy hour 15:00-20:00. Classic Viennese style with chandeliers.

name: Sling
description: Leather and fetish bar for gay men in Wieden district. Club, bar and cruising lounge open daily. Features free entry with no dress code except special events. Nearest station U4 Kettenbrückengasse. Best time to visit after 20:00.

name: Vorspiel
description: Venue requiring additional verification - specific information not found in web searches. May be former venue, alternate name, or smaller establishment not widely documented.

name: Red Carpet
description: One of Vienna's busiest gay bars, voted best queer-mixed bar in Austria. Largest queer-mixed location in Vienna featuring bar, lounge, and dance floor. Note: Some sources indicate possible closure - verify status before visiting.

name: Augenblick
description: LGBT-friendly café bar in Neubau district (7th district) with cultivated hospitality. Features summer garden, exquisite wines, beer selection, selected liqueurs and cocktails, Viennese coffee specialties, and food. Vienna City Card 20% discount available.

name: Palmenhaus
description: Café, brasserie and bar in historic Art Nouveau greenhouse built for Austrian emperors. Located in Burggarten behind Hofburg Palace. Features exotic flora setting with terrace overlooking garden. Serves breakfast, lunch and dinner in extravagant steel-and-glass Jugendstil structure.

name: Café Flinte
description: Women-only (transgender welcome) FLINT café in Josefstadt district since 1977. Queer feminist association and collectively organized space for projects and events. Run by committed lesbians targeting female and trans audience. Admission policy: women, lesbians, inter, non-binary, trans only.

name: Club-U
description: Small student-favourite bar-club in Otto Wagner Pavilion Art Nouveau building at Karlsplatz. Wide range of events with music from Soul to Hip-Hop and Techno. Features wonderful outdoor seating area with regular DJs.

name: Le Studio
description: Film festival venue - specific information not found. Traditional Viennale (Vienna International Film Festival) venues include Gartenbaukino, Urania, Metro-Kino, Filmmuseum and Stadtkino. May be alternate name or smaller venue.

name: Admiralkino
description: Beautiful arthouse cinema in District 7 operating since 1913. Hosts film festivals, readings and special events. Features 'Doggy Day' first Thursday of each month (dogs attend free). Wheelchair accessible. Managed by Wiktoria Pelzer since January 2023.

name: Filmcasino
description: One of Vienna's oldest cinemas established in 1911 with signature 50s-look. Art-house, indie, and international cinema venue. Hosts /slash Filmfestival, CineLatino, Identities Queer Film Festival and short film festivals. Located in Margareten district.
